GREP

grep "user" "/wk/config.txt" (search for user in config file)
grep -c "user" "/wk/config.txt" (search for number of line contains user)
grep -v "user" "/wk/config.txt" (search for line does'nt contain user in config file)
grep -R "user" /etc/config/ (search recursively in each file of the folder the line who contains user)
grep -w "user" "/wk/config.txt" (Search for word user)
grep -in "user" "/wk/config.txt" (case insensitive and print the line number in the file)
